task.summary: Default task
Fix in view module
Added confine functionality to Field
Reorganized directories
Finished printer, not tested
Added method rectangles_in_contact to Area which returns a list of all rectangles which & with the argument is not None. Usefull for detecting area corners.
-Fixed a bug in assigning area's in some cases -New method for field - is_free_corner, which detects if the corner is not touching any other rectangles -Fixed an indexing issue in printer
Added parent to Area - method get_root to get the parent Renamed some of the tests- minor
Changed the Rectangle area mechanic, now there will be only one root-area, which will be the self.area field of every area added to the said area
Added method returning free corners to Rectangle
Changed characters of printer a bit
Area will now check whether new rectangles added using += operator coincide with existing ones and raise Exception accordingly.

Distinguish between corners that are free and free diagonally - diagonally is subset of the general term - is a corner is free it is free diagonally, if it's free diagonally it is not necessarily free

- Fixed a bug in calculating size() of rectangles - Major: Added methods for detecting contact with other rectangles, both vertical as well as horizontal - Contact method always sorts the arguments according to size, what makes it asymmetric, which was needed for proper contact detection, this must be changed eventurally ; change cannot destroy previously added capabilities, tests are unfinished pending dev
Added method is_joinable(other) to rectangle, will be used with join method which is on the way
- Major: added method join() to rectangle, checks the conditions and performs all the operations, checks in with the area for changes
Added basic loading of maps
Fix in joining rectangles
Loader work in progress, giving not perfect results
Commented most of code, some refactoring done

Added Walker class which walks :)
The moves are checked for accessibility and not leading to standing in place but their range is not checked, for now,=

Added path to Walker
Some refactoring

Added new class Corner which is a child of Field class
Essentially takes functionality from base class with one exception: It has a member CornerType which is a Enum representing offset needed for raytracing.
Added points with floating point coordinates for raytracing
Conversion from Field and Corner to Point, bug fixes
ViewGenerator development; will now sort Fields for raytracing

Reorganized project structure
Circular dependencies were removed using deferred import
Fixed angles in points, now they will map properly
Sorting done by viewGenerator is fully working.
Work toward making rays
Moved part of the logic of out the Field class, will use for Point
Fixing some problems with previous commits
Point is now inheriting from TwoCoordinate and thus can be tested for being inside a rectangle
Changed the behaviour of operator >= for TwoCoordinate
Rays now can be checked for validity, this means raytracing is now possible
Initial work into light map, few other fixes
Light map working brilliantly
Lightmap and view are now working, printing of view possible
Added a pheromone map
PheromoneMap updated to transitions, not points
Upgraded the hash, which now has 2x the performance
Upgraded results

A lot of refactoring:
-Added Move class, will now check for it's validity on it's own -Pheromone maps now have move class as keys -Moved is_field_accessible to Area
Large performance tweaks with Field constructor
Some testing
Encapsulation of simulation :)
Fix in evaporation
More vaporisation
